    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's more than just sensitivity though. \"intuition\" implies I'm just guessing, but I'm not. It was like a physical pressure. and the weirdest part is that when I look at things that are about to happen, they dont just feel heavy, they feel... static. like the object is stuck between then and now. i was thinking about it more and i think i'm actually starting to see the patterns in how it happens. like, there has to be a logic to it, right? like a way to actually use it or understand the mechanics of how the \"echo\" works. do you think there's a way to study this or figure out the actual rules of how these traces manifest?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
